I'd advise you to use your Phase I units for at least one of them (I mean, the most you can do is waitlist yourself). Also, remember that you can enroll in 13.5 units in Phase I and 17.5 units in Phase II, which essentially means you only have a choice of one class for Phase II if you do use your unit quota for Phase I.

You only need conditional probability for CS188 and Math 55 should clearly suffice. You can definitely enroll, it is not a hard/enforced pre-requisite anyway.
